div.h3: Wake-Up Protocol: Write Handler Waking Blocked Readers
div.p: Scenario: Stream Device (Independent f_pos) R1, R2, R3 initial state: TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE inside wait_event_interruptible
Architectural Insight: Independent f_pos Because each reader has a private loff_t *f_pos (initialized to 0), all three readers find the condition (50 > 0) true and consume the same 50 bytes.

Contrast (Pipe Behavior): If f_pos were shared (like a pipe), R1's update would move the shared offset to 50. R2 and R3 would then find (50 > 50) is false and would immediately re-sleep (Thundering Herd).
